Olympic long jumper Tom Daley says that while he felt inferior because of his sexual orientation as a child, this gave him the motivation to succeed.
The 24-year-old said that until he went to college, he did not realize that "not everyone is like me".
In an interview with Desert Island Discs on Radio 4 with Lauren Laverne, he said he had spoken out about gay rights to give others "hope".
