He said: "To this day, those feelings, the feeling of being less and the feeling of being different, are real facts that have given me the strength to succeed".
He wanted to prove that he was "somebody" so that he would not disappoint people if they eventually found out about his nature.
The two-time Olympic bronze medallist has become a prominent campaigner for the LGBT community and used his presence at this year's Commonwealth Games in Australia to call for more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said that he spoke out because he considered himself fortunate to be able to live openly without further consequences and because he wanted to give others "hope".
The three-time world champion said that the fact that he fell in love with a man, American filmmaker Dustin Lance Back, whom he met in 2013, "has completely surprised me".
Daley married the Oscar winner last year, who is 20 years older than him, but said the age difference had never been a problem.
