Thomas Bjorn, captain of the European team, knows that a big lead can quickly disappear
Thomas Bjorn, the captain of the European team, knows from experience that the comfortable lead ahead of the singles matches on the final day of the Ryder Cup can easily turn into a less comfortable situation.
The Dane made his debut in the 1997 Valderrama match, where the team captained by Seve Ballesteros had a five-point lead over the Americans, but eventually crossed the finish line by the smallest possible margin: 141⁄2-131⁄2.
