Foreign buyers will have to pay higher levies when buying a house in the UK
Foreign buyers will have to pay higher levies when buying a house in the UK and the proceeds will be used to help the homeless, according to new plans by the Conservatives.
This action will have to neutralize Corbyn's success to attract young voters
The increase in levies is levied on persons who do not pay tax in the UK
The Treasury expects this to raise £120 million a year to help the homeless.
Foreign buyers will have to pay higher taxes when buying a house in the UK and the extra proceeds will be used to help the homeless, Theresa May will announce today.
